# Commits and PRs

## Format: Conventional Commits

```
<type>(<scope>): <imperative subject in lowercase>

<body explaining WHY, wrapped at ~80 chars, optional but encouraged>
```

### Allowed types

| Type | Use for |
|---|---|
| `feat` | user-visible new behavior |
| `fix` | user-visible bug fix |
| `refactor` | internal restructure, no behavior change |
| `perf` | performance improvement |
| `test` | adding or improving tests only |
| `docs` | docs, README, comments |
| `chore` | tooling, deps, build, gitignore, configs |
| `style` | formatting only (rare; usually rolled into another type) |
| `build` | build system or external deps |
| `ci` | CI configuration |

### Scope

Use the most specific name available, e.g. `stage`, `node`, `graph`,
`layout`, `physics`, `multigraph`, `repo`, `storybook`, `deps`.

### Examples

```
feat(graph): add togglePinned mutation with hops recomputation
fix(stage): release pointer capture on pointercancel during pinch
refactor(stage): unify single-click drag into onNodeMoved
test(layout): cover scaleByHops floor and falloff edge cases
chore(deps): bump @storybook/addon-vitest to ^10.3
docs(roadmap): mark milestone 02 complete and link to plan
```

## One logical change per commit

Don't mix a refactor with a feature. Don't mix gitignore changes with code
changes. If you find yourself writing "and" in a commit subject, split it.

## Body explains WHY, not WHAT

The diff already shows what changed. The body should explain why this change
exists, what alternatives you considered, and any non-obvious constraints.

## Before committing

- Generated files (`.svelte-kit/`, `*storybook*.log`, build outputs) must
  not be in the staged diff. If they are, your `.gitignore` is broken.
- Tests for the change must already pass locally (see `core.mdc` Definition of Done).

## PRs

- Title = lead commit subject (Conventional Commits format).
- Description = the "Definition of Done" checklist from
  `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`, filled in.
- Link the milestone doc the PR is delivering against.
